news.title: China's land sales slump for second month as property chill bites
news.para: The value of land sales nationwide fell 11.15% to 570.3 billion yuan ($89 billion) from a year earlier, according to Reuters calculations of finance ministry data released on Friday, after sinking 17.5% in August.

news.title: China Evergrande lines up funds to pay interest, avert default for now: Source
news.para: China's second-largest property developer sent $83.5 million to a Citibank trustee account on Thursday, the person with knowledge of the matter told Reuters, enabling it to pay interest on a U.S. dollar bond due by Oct. 23.

news.title: Fill vacant urban development and housing posts: Rajasthan CM
news.para: The CM was speaking during a review meet of the ambitious campaign on Thursday. The CM will also visit the camps organised under 'Prashan Gaon Ke Sangh' campaign in Nagaur and Jaipur districts on Friday.

news.title: Chinese tax agency investigating SOHO China unit for suspected tax evasion
news.para: The announcement comes amid a flurry of anti-monopoly and other enforcement actions against internet and other private companies as the ruling Communist Party tightens control over the economy.

news.title: Properties bought after parting ways not part of joint family: Karnataka HC
news.para: The observation was made while setting aside a February 9, 2017 order passed by a civil court in Bengaluru in relation to a partition suit involving children and grandchildren of LC Shettaiah.

news.title: Jaipur: Development plan of Walled City to be prepared in one month
news.para: This decision was taken in the recent heritage committee meeting held under the chairmanship of G S Sandhu, advisor to the state government. The plan will be prepared on the basis of the guidelines given by UNESCO.

news.title: 'Builders' cheat Delhi businessman of Rs 1.5 crore by selling floor, booked
news.para: Hansh Raj (69), a resident of West Punjabi Bagh, got in touch with Gurbani Kaur and Jasmeet Singh, residents of DLF-2 in January 2018. Gurbani and Jasmeet introduced themselves as builders and informed Hansh Raj that they are constructing builder floors on a 270 square yard of plot in Qutub Enclave in DLF-4.

news.title: SC-appointed CEC asks Assam government to crack whip on illegal construction
news.para: The report noted that there has been a “gross violation” of the apex court order and said the illegal constructions have to be “demolished” whether it is just a small shack, dhaba or concrete house or restaurant.

news.title: Chandigarh: Panel reviews process to streamline property services
news.para: The panel discussed streamlining the process of mutation of property through sale deed, transfer of lease rights by sale, grant of no-objection certificate and certificate of unearned profit under Rule 1973 and 2007.

news.title: Nagpur: Praful Ved Infrastructure wins bid to construct Metro Mall
news.para: Confirming this, municipal commissioner Radhakrishnan B told TOI that the NMC had floated tenders to appoint a private agency to build eight floors comprising a shopping mall, restaurant and a multiplex with rooftop eatery.

news.title: Uttarakhand HC seeks reply on PIL regarding construction without maps
news.para: Kotdwar resident Mujeeb Naithani has filed the PIL, saying that the government had created district development authorities (DDAs) in many districts in 2016.

news.title: Gurugram: HSVP to develop residential plots on gymkhana club land in Sector 55
news.para: The urban development authority, in fact, plans to develop the 1.4-acre land into 26 residential plots and sell the same to raise over Rs 50 crore.

news.title: Tamil Nadu: Property registrations bring record-high revenue in September
news.para: Income from property and land registrations in Tamil Nadu in September was nearly Rs 1,500 crore — the highest in a month in any year.

news.title: Poor response to gunthewari regularisation in Aurangabad
news.para: While development charges of Rs 1,140 per square metre are levied for regularisation of gunthewari property, the applicant also must pay compounding charges and scrutiny charges, among other fees, as a part of the regularisation.

news.title: WeWork shares jump on debut after two-year struggle to go public
news.para: "WeWork has a low occupancy rate, 55-58% recently, and thus can grow revenue without increasing costs by very much. It needs to grow revenue, because it is currently losing close to $1 for every dollar of revenue that it brings in," IPO expert Jay Ritter, a professor at the University of Florida, said.
